com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method
Interface NativeConstructor

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehavior, NativeCapable
All Known Subinterfaces:
CPPConstructor, NativeConstructorCallback, NativeConstructorReflection, NativeDirectConstructorCallback
public interface NativeConstructor
extends NativeBehavior

The NativeConstructor is the interface implemented by native capable classes that bridges Java and native constructors.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

call

java.lang.Object call(java.lang.Object[] args)
Calls the native constructor.

The specified arguments must match the native type of the method parameters. Returned value type will match the native type of the declared class.

Parameters:
args - the arguments passed to the method.
Returns:
the new constructed native object.

call

void call(java.lang.Object proxy,
          java.lang.Object[] args)
Calls the native constructor using an instance as proxy of the returned address of the created object.

The specified arguments must match the native type of the method parameters. Returned value type will match the native type of the declared class.

The proxy argument must be a native capable instance of the class of the constructor. This proxy will be attached to the returned address of the native constructor call.

Parameters:
proxy - the native capable object used as proxy.
args - the arguments passed to the method.
See Also:
NativeManager.attach(Object,long)
